# Rust Systems & Cloud Infrastructure Guide

Vertical deepening of rust-architecture-guide for long-running cloud-native services. Based on [rust-systems-cloud-infra-guide](/opt/pdf-module/.cursor/skills/rust-systems-cloud-infra-guide/SKILL.md) V6.1.0.

## Core Principles

| Principle | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| **Mechanical Sympathy** | Align software with hardware physics (CPU cache, NUMA, kernel I/O stack) |
| **Determinism** | Eliminate non-determinism for reproducible state machines |
| **Resilience** | Graceful degradation over crash; backpressure over OOM |
| **Jeet Kune Do** | One-strike memory lifecycle; flow like water to hardware channels |

## Red Lines (Prohibitions)

| Category | Prohibited | Mandatory |
|----------|------------|-----------|
| Queue | `std::sync::mpsc::channel()` unbounded | `tokio::sync::mpsc::channel(LIMIT)` |
| Cancellation | Direct non-idempotent write in `select!` | `spawn` + `oneshot` |
| Time | `Instant::now()` in state machine Apply | Leader-proposed timestamp |
| Shutdown | Exit immediately on `SIGTERM` | Graceful shutdown flow (CancellationToken â†’ drain â†’ persist â†’ exit) |
| FFI | `extern` function without `catch_unwind` | Catch panic + return error code |
| Per-Request Alloc | Global heap for AST nodes | Arena (`bumpalo`) |
| Arena Escape | Save Arena ptr to external static | Clone to global heap if needed |
| Alloc Panic | `panic!` on exhaustion | `Result<T, AllocError>` + backpressure (503) |
| Read-heavy Lock | `RwLock`/`Mutex` in read-heavy path | `arc-swap` (RCU zero-block read) |
| Memory Ordering | Blind `Ordering::SeqCst` | `Release`+`Acquire` pair; `Relaxed` for counters |
| Byte Loop | Byte-by-byte `if byte == b'\n'` | SIMD bitmask bulk compare |
| AoS | Array of Structs for bulk aggregation | SoA (Struct of Arrays) columnar layout |

## Key Actions

1. **I/O Model**: Many TCP conns â†’ `tokio`+`epoll`; high disk throughput â†’ `monoio`/`glommio` (io_uring); **never mix runtimes**
2. **Zero-Copy**: Kernel-level `splice`/`sendfile` via `rustix`; user-space `bytes::Bytes` for O(1) clone
3. **Graceful Shutdown**: SIGTERM â†’ CancellationToken â†’ stop new requests â†’ drain in-flight â†’ fsync WAL â†’ exit
4. **Deterministic State Machine**: Prohibit `Instant::now()`, `SystemTime::now()`, `rand::random()`, `HashMap` order; use `BTreeMap`/`IndexMap`
5. **Lock-free Read Path**: Use `arc-swap`; writer does Copyâ†’Modifyâ†’Swap; readers never block
6. **SIMD Vectorized**: Use `std::simd` or `core::arch::x86_64` (AVX-512); convert control flow to data flow via Bitmask
7. **Slab Pre-allocation**: `mmap` large contiguous block at startup; `crossbeam_queue::ArrayQueue` for lock-free alloc/dealloc
